ame":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Isabella Astbury was born in Blackpool, England, in 2014.\n\nIsabella's love for filmmaking began at age four when she watched 'E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial.' The film's magic sparked her dream of becoming a part of the world of cinema. In 2017, Isabella took a bold step in her journey by moving to Canada. Today, she calls both Canada and the UK home, holding citizenship for both countries to pursue her acting career and also hoping to land a role in the US.\n\nIsabella's acting journey started with her role in the short film \"Seabreeze,\" where she showcased her passion for the craft at a young age of 6. Isabella made her mark at Monologue Slam Canada during Covid pandemic, winning three times from 2020 to 2022, establishing herself in the Canadian acting scene. In 2022, Isabella excelled on the global stage at the World Monologue Slam, earning first place in the judges' choice and a Silver Award.\n\nIsabella continues to improve her skills with training at the LeBlanc School of Acting as well as other international coaches\n\n- IMDb mini biography by: Sabrina Astbury","name":"Isabella Astbury","primary":true}}]}},"movie_417609_keywords":{"at":1773319436025,"data":{"id":417609,"keywords":[]}},"person_1964729_translations":{"at":1773319436740,"data":{"id":1964729,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Meerim Atantaeva","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KG","iso_639_1":"ky","name":"??????","english_name":"Kirghiz","data":{"biography":"","name":"Meerim Atantaeva","primary":true}}]}},"person_6057798_translations":{"at":1773405759936,"data":{"id":6057798,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Katherine Solari","prima